facts.text: U. P. Union Bank Ltd. was tenant of a building in Agra town belonging to the respondent at monthly rental of Rs. 325 and Rs. 10 as municipal taxes.

anchor.surface_text: The Judgment of the Court was delivered by SHAH J.-The U. P. Union Bank Ltd.  which will hereinafter be referred to as the Bank  was in occupation as a tenant of a building in Agra town belonging to the respondent. at a monthly rental of Rs. 325 and Rs. 10 as municipal taxes.

facts.text: The Bank made default in paying the rent accruing due.

facts.text: Munsiff decreed the suit on December 2, 1949 and confirmed the attachment before judgment.

facts.text: On a petition dated September 13, 1949, the High Court ordered the Bank to be wound up and appointed the appellants as liquidators.

facts.text: Employees of the Bank vacated the premises on September 10, 1949.

facts.text: On November 30, 1950, respondent applied to High Court for permission to file suit for ejectment and arrears of rent since September 30, 1949.

facts.text: Mr. Justice Mootham by order dated August 30, 1951 held landlord entitled to rent at Rs. 325 per mensem from October 1, 1949 upto date Official Liquidators give possession terminating tenancy.

anchor.surface_text: By order dated August 30, 1951, Mr. Justice Mootham I hold that the petitioner is entitled to recover rent from the Bank at the rate of Rs. 325 per mensem from 1st October, 1949, upto the date on which the Official Liquidators give the petitioner  the landlord  such possession of the premises as will, in law, terminate the Banks tenancy.

facts.text: Official Liquidators preferred special appeal No. 17 of 1952 against Mootham J order.

facts.text: High Court by order dated April 17, 1956 directed Official Liquidators to pay respondent in full the rent due after October 1, 1949.
